ad Paul Graham’s Acceleration of Addictiveness where he compares addictive technology to alcohol and cigarette [&hellip;]''>Matt: Culture of Distraction</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://blog.akismet.com/2012/05/30/50-billion-little-piece/'' title=''Akismet passed another milestone: we caught our 50 billionth piece of spam yesterday. TechCrunch has the details: In April, Akismet blocked 1.8 billion spam messages, or 60 million pieces of spam per day, 2.5 million per hour, or 700 per second. Whoa, that’s a lot of spam. Akismet, those with long memories will recall, was the first product Automattic ever l [&hellip;]''>Akismet: 50 Billion Little Pieces</a></li></ul></div>', 'no'),
